These are the simple steps which we will follow in our program

Step 1- Load the driver

Step 2-Create a connection

Step 3- Create a statement

Step 4- Execute your query

Step 5- Store the data in Result set

Step 6- Verify whether data (table) is updated or not

NOTE: If you want to connect with local database. Set the DSN in control panel.
Control Panel > Administrative Tool > Click on ODBC -> Add


About the project
Run the CreateLead.java. It will create a lead in leaftaps
and then pass the lead id to verify
We will then query the database and see if the lead id exists.